WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.869
           NARRATOR:
       <i> Once upon a time,</i>

00:03.904 --> 00:06.638
     <i> in a mythical place</i>
     <i> called Cape Kennedy,</i>

00:06.673 --> 00:10.375
<i> an astronaut named Tony Nelson</i>
  <i> went up on a space mission.</i>

00:10.410 --> 00:11.844
     <i> The missile went up,</i>

00:11.879 --> 00:15.346
   <i> but something went wrong,</i>
<i> and they had to bring it down.</i>

00:15.382 --> 00:19.417
   <i> Captain Nelson landed on</i>
<i>an island in the South Pacific,</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.186
   <i> where he found a bottle.</i>

00:21.221 --> 00:23.088
           <i> At least,</i>
   <i> it looked like a bottle.</i>

00:23.123 --> 00:25.690
       <i> But it didn't act</i>
        <i> like a bottle.</i>

00:25.725 --> 00:26.858
             [♪♪♪]

00:26.893 --> 00:29.394
  <i> Because in it was a genie.</i>

00:29.429 --> 00:31.964
     <i> Oh, not your average,</i>
        <i> everyday genie,</i>

00:31.999 --> 00:33.999
   <i> but a beautiful genie...</i>

00:35.035 --> 00:37.536
 <i> ...who could grant</i> any <i> wish.</i>

00:37.571 --> 00:39.437
             [♪♪♪]

01:02.263 --> 01:05.564
<i>Captain Nelson was so grateful,</i>
     <i> he set Jeannie free,</i>

01:05.599 --> 01:06.965
     <i> only she didn't want</i>
          <i> to be free.</i>

01:07.000 --> 01:08.567
      <i> You know how it is</i>

01:08.602 --> 01:12.003
  <i> when you've been cooped up</i>
  <i> in a bottle for 2000 years.</i>

01:12.039 --> 01:13.605
    <i> She wanted to have fun.</i>

01:13.641 --> 01:16.441
   <i> And she wanted to have it</i>
     <i> with Captain Nelson.</i>

01:16.477 --> 01:19.044
   <i> So she followed him back</i>
        <i> to Cocoa Beach,</i>

01:19.079 --> 01:20.179
        <i> a mythical town</i>

01:20.214 --> 01:23.148
      <i> in a mythical state</i>
        <i> called Florida.</i>

01:23.183 --> 01:24.483
   <i> And there in this house,</i>

01:24.518 --> 01:27.786
    <i> the girl in the bottle</i>
   <i> plays Spin the Astronaut.</i>

01:27.821 --> 01:29.821
             [♪♪♪]

02:00.820 --> 02:02.053
             Hi.

02:03.723 --> 02:05.390
I thought
you went to sleep.

02:09.997 --> 02:12.063
               I thought you
          went to sleep, master.

02:12.099 --> 02:14.266
No, no. I decided
to work on my model.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.500
Isn't it a beauty?

02:15.535 --> 02:18.236
            Mmm. Very nice.

02:22.175 --> 02:23.608
       [SIGHS]

02:25.445 --> 02:27.612
 You must be hungry.
                     Uh-uh.

02:27.647 --> 02:30.048
Well, you ate hardly
anything for dinner.

02:32.953 --> 02:34.185
      [GIGGLES]

02:34.221 --> 02:35.186
       [SNIFFS]

02:35.222 --> 02:37.322
       [SIGHS]

02:37.357 --> 02:40.058
I almost made it myself.

02:42.762 --> 02:43.861
You know what is in it?

02:43.897 --> 02:46.064
             Yes, 4000 calories.

02:46.099 --> 02:47.332
       Tsk.

02:47.367 --> 02:49.000
       [WHINES]

02:53.340 --> 02:54.705
                [CLEARS THROAT]

02:54.741 --> 02:56.341
   You are without
    shoes again.

02:56.376 --> 02:57.775
  I will go fetch
  your slippers.

02:57.811 --> 02:59.877
     No, no, no, please.
 Don't bother. Don't bother.

02:59.913 --> 03:01.346
                  It's no bother
                 at all, master.

03:01.381 --> 03:02.780
I don't like being
  fussed over--

03:02.816 --> 03:04.916
When I'm working,
I don't like being fussed over.

03:04.952 --> 03:07.419
         But, master, I do not--
Please don't call me "master."

03:07.454 --> 03:09.387
It makes me feel like
a fat old caliph.

03:09.423 --> 03:13.658
                Oh, thou art
            neither old nor fat.

03:13.693 --> 03:15.160
         Thou art most handsome.

03:15.195 --> 03:16.627
        Am I?
                  Mmm.

03:16.663 --> 03:17.829
   What did I do
   with that glue?

03:17.864 --> 03:19.197
             Oh, I'll get it.
    Hey, hey, hey!

03:19.232 --> 03:20.398
Now, be careful.

03:20.434 --> 03:22.100
Look, I put a lot
of time in on this.

03:22.135 --> 03:24.069
               Do I not know it.

03:24.104 --> 03:27.372
              Every night,
       to fashion a child's toy.

03:27.407 --> 03:29.174
It's not
a child's toy.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.508
    This is an exact replica

03:30.543 --> 03:32.177
   of the one we're gonna use
          next month.

03:32.212 --> 03:34.612
            Master?

03:34.647 --> 03:36.081
  There's a moon out tonight.

03:36.116 --> 03:38.516
    Would it not be pleasant
   to stroll along the beach?

03:38.551 --> 03:40.585
            Hm-hmm.

03:40.620 --> 03:42.854
          Yeah. Yeah,
     why don't you do that.

03:43.690 --> 03:45.490
     [SPEAKS IN ARABIC DIALECT]

03:47.160 --> 03:48.793
             There.

03:48.828 --> 03:49.961
       There, it's done.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.064
How about that, huh?

03:53.100 --> 03:54.499
Looks real enough
to blast off,

03:54.534 --> 03:55.967
 doesn't it, hm?

04:06.446 --> 04:07.445
                  [GIGGLES]

04:08.681 --> 04:12.017
           Well, master, back
       to the old drawing board.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.923
             [♪♪♪]

04:22.329 --> 04:24.295
             [♪♪♪]

04:35.509 --> 04:37.308
                 [CHUCKLES]

04:38.845 --> 04:40.378
                   What art thou
                    laughing at?

04:40.414 --> 04:43.047
 Uh-- Well, it's a little funny.
  What are you reading, Jeannie?

04:43.082 --> 04:44.248
           I'm reading a scroll.

04:44.284 --> 04:48.720
"The Eman-ci-pa-tion
of Modern Woman."

04:48.755 --> 04:50.321
What does it mean?

04:50.356 --> 04:52.156
            Jeannie-- Oh,
          you don't have to

04:52.191 --> 04:53.491
         worry about
       things like that.

04:53.527 --> 04:55.893
Oh, but I do.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.729
I want to understand
your way of life,

04:57.764 --> 04:59.297
so that I can please you.

04:59.333 --> 05:00.699
             Well, you please me
                  very much.

05:00.734 --> 05:03.201
       Matter of fact, you're...
            You're perfect.

05:03.237 --> 05:05.303
     [GIGGLES]

05:05.339 --> 05:07.272
Dost thou really think so?

05:07.307 --> 05:09.173
                 Yes. Yes, I do.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.943
     Oh, uh, do you have to say,
             "dost thou"?

05:11.978 --> 05:13.110
               We say, "do you."

05:13.146 --> 05:14.646
     Oh.

05:14.681 --> 05:16.314
Do you think it would
be possible for me

05:16.349 --> 05:18.182
to view the sights
of your village tonight?

05:18.217 --> 05:19.250
                 Why, certainly.

05:19.286 --> 05:20.452
[CHUCKLES]
                    [CHUCKLES]

05:20.487 --> 05:22.587
                      Oh--
                   Oh, no, no.

05:22.622 --> 05:23.721
  Why not?

05:23.756 --> 05:25.557
              Well, it's the way
                you're dressed.

05:25.592 --> 05:27.792
You look like a fugitive
from a costume party.

05:29.162 --> 05:31.996
Well-- How should
I dress?

05:32.031 --> 05:33.631
               Oh, I don't know.
                     Uh...

05:33.666 --> 05:34.932
                  Why don't you
                pick out someone

05:34.968 --> 05:36.734
               that dresses well
                 and copy them.

05:38.004 --> 05:39.404
    [GIGGLES]

05:39.439 --> 05:41.339
         No, no. I-I don't think
            you get the idea.

05:41.374 --> 05:43.007
Oh, but you do dress well.

05:43.042 --> 05:44.375
                 Well, thank you
                    very much.

05:44.411 --> 05:46.578
        But I-I wish you'd stop
      these silly little tricks.

05:48.315 --> 05:52.016
So...except for the manner
in which I speak,

05:52.051 --> 05:54.785
   dress and act...

05:54.821 --> 05:56.053
   I am perfect?

05:56.089 --> 05:58.356
         That's right. Now,
    you just keep working at it.

05:58.391 --> 06:00.825
               Remember...
         practice makes perfect.

06:00.860 --> 06:02.994
          I'm a little late now.
           I'll see you tonight.

06:05.532 --> 06:06.498
            [SIGHS]

06:06.533 --> 06:08.600
                   [DOOR CLOSES]

06:08.635 --> 06:11.135
        Master! Master!

06:13.139 --> 06:15.106
[CAR ZOOMS AWAY]

06:20.080 --> 06:21.746
       Hiya,
  Captain Nelson!

06:21.781 --> 06:23.648
How's
the old boy?

06:36.863 --> 06:40.197
 "Are you a loser in the battle
      between the sexes?"

06:40.233 --> 06:42.466
              Mmm.

06:42.502 --> 06:45.436
"Is the man in your life aloof,
      indifferent to you,

06:45.471 --> 06:46.771
     impossible to please?"

06:46.806 --> 06:48.239
             Mm-hm.

06:48.274 --> 06:50.542
  "Does he fail to appreciate
     what you have to offer

06:50.577 --> 06:52.343
   as a person, as a female?"

06:52.378 --> 06:55.179
   Hm. The answer is obvious.

06:55.214 --> 06:57.214
    "The answer is obvious."

06:57.250 --> 06:59.050
      "One, you must learn
        how to challenge

06:59.085 --> 07:01.653
   his masculine arrogance."

07:01.688 --> 07:03.821
      [CHUCKLES WICKEDLY]

07:03.857 --> 07:07.725
 "Two, you must be independent,
  self-reliant, unpredictable.

07:09.195 --> 07:12.864
 "Three, you must learn to cope
  with him on his own grounds.

07:12.899 --> 07:17.802
   In short, you must become
   a modern American woman."

07:25.278 --> 07:27.679
             ROGER:
Check manual-mode ECS operation.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.649
                    TONY:
               Manual mode ECS
                satisfactory.

07:33.486 --> 07:35.820
Check O-2 tanks
one and two pressures.

07:37.724 --> 07:39.023
                   [CLICK]

07:39.059 --> 07:41.593
              O-2 tank pressure:
                 400 p.s.i.a.

07:43.597 --> 07:44.996
           [SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

07:48.068 --> 07:49.834
       BELLOWS:
Check suit temperature.

07:51.370 --> 07:53.537
  Suit temperature is low.

07:53.573 --> 07:55.339
                      Check suit
                       pressure.

07:55.374 --> 07:57.876
 Suit pressure normal.

07:57.911 --> 07:59.577
          I'm feeling
     a little light-headed.

07:59.612 --> 08:01.946
  Switch to your manual
    auxiliary oxygen.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.114
  You hear me, Tony?

08:03.149 --> 08:04.649
          I hear you.

08:06.987 --> 08:08.954
 Now give me a reading
 on your oxygen supply.

08:10.891 --> 08:13.959
     O-2 flow is...normal.

08:15.963 --> 08:17.195
      Ugh! Okay.

08:17.230 --> 08:18.362
I'll bring you down, Tony.

08:18.398 --> 08:19.598
                        TONY:
                        <i> Roger. </i>
        Yeah?

08:19.633 --> 08:21.333
         I mean, roger,
        I'm coming down.

08:21.368 --> 08:22.334
          Oh.

08:22.369 --> 08:23.801
    [CLEARS THROAT]

08:38.986 --> 08:40.251
                       Hi, Roge.

08:40.287 --> 08:42.287
       Must have been a blockage
          in the oxygen valve.

08:42.322 --> 08:43.520
Oh, we'll
have it checked.

08:43.556 --> 08:44.789
             How are
            we feeling?

08:44.824 --> 08:46.091
                    Hungry, sir.

08:46.126 --> 08:48.759
      Well, didn't you eat
    your tube of roast beef?

08:48.795 --> 08:50.228
                   That's what
                 made me hungry.

08:50.263 --> 08:51.863
          I'll see you
    in the morning, captain.

08:51.898 --> 08:53.331
                     All right.
   Get dressed.

08:53.367 --> 08:54.932
I got a real treat
for you.

08:54.968 --> 08:57.335
I found the greatest
Chinese restaurant

08:57.371 --> 08:59.871
run by a Greek,
and the egg foo yung, mmm.

08:59.906 --> 09:01.172
                  You'll have to
                   count me out.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.474
                  I'm gonna have
                 dinner at home.

09:02.509 --> 09:04.342
How did you swing that,
old bachelor buddy?

09:04.378 --> 09:06.978
       Um... Well, I have a girl
        who comes in part-time.

09:07.014 --> 09:08.279
And she cooks
dinner for you?

09:08.315 --> 09:09.381
                     Yeah, sure.
                    Every night.

09:09.416 --> 09:11.082
Well, where did you
find this treasure?

09:11.118 --> 09:12.650
            I, uh, picked her up
                on the beach.

09:12.685 --> 09:14.119
                  See you, Roge.
        Uh, uh.

09:14.154 --> 09:15.520
            Think you could have
                  this girl

09:15.555 --> 09:16.821
             cook for both of us
                 some night?

09:16.856 --> 09:18.323
     No, no, no.
You wouldn't like it.

09:18.358 --> 09:20.125
She's a terrible cook.

09:25.632 --> 09:28.266
         Jeannie! Home!

09:40.847 --> 09:42.380
     Well, what's going on?

09:47.020 --> 09:48.920
         Ahem. Jeannie.

09:48.955 --> 09:50.722
        Are you there?!

09:51.958 --> 09:52.991
            Jeannie?

09:53.026 --> 09:54.025
          [KICKS BAG]

10:10.043 --> 10:12.877
               Now, what is
              going on here?

10:13.880 --> 10:14.979
            Jeannie.

10:17.150 --> 10:18.249
        [KICKS BAG]

10:20.020 --> 10:21.118
                 Oh! There--

10:21.154 --> 10:22.353
     Hiya, master!

10:22.388 --> 10:23.988
How's the old boy?

10:24.024 --> 10:26.157
           How's the old boy?
       What have you been doing?

10:26.192 --> 10:28.426
I've been doing nothing.
        Yeah, well, I know that,

10:28.461 --> 10:30.394
but I mean,
what <i> have</i> you been doing?

10:30.430 --> 10:31.462
          I have been studying

10:31.497 --> 10:33.665
               the "Emancipation
               of Modern Woman."

10:33.700 --> 10:36.200
Oh. Oh, that. I guess
you got so caught up in it,

10:36.235 --> 10:37.635
you forgot to do
 the housework?

10:37.671 --> 10:38.836
           Oh, I did not forget.

10:38.872 --> 10:40.471
                   I decided to
                  let you do it.

10:40.506 --> 10:41.573
   Wh-- Me?

10:42.676 --> 10:45.577
             "How not to be
               a drudge.

10:45.612 --> 10:47.144
       Share the work with him."

10:47.180 --> 10:48.947
Now, come on--
          That's what it says.

10:48.982 --> 10:51.182
Yeah, but that advice
is for ordinary women.

10:51.217 --> 10:52.584
Now, you're not
ordinary women.

10:52.619 --> 10:54.052
You're a genie, Jeannie.

10:54.087 --> 10:57.055
I mean, all you have to do
is bat your eyes, and presto!

10:57.090 --> 10:58.890
               No more presto.

10:58.925 --> 11:00.792
            You must not take me
                for granted.

11:00.827 --> 11:03.494
Y-- I never did that
in my-- I never--

11:03.529 --> 11:04.963
And besides,
I'm an astronaut.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.030
I'm not a housekeeper.

11:06.066 --> 11:07.531
                     Mmm.

11:07.567 --> 11:08.866
                You must widen
                your horizons.

11:08.902 --> 11:10.267
Yes. And you must
take a little--

11:10.303 --> 11:12.303
          Here, I have a present
                 for you.

11:12.338 --> 11:13.404
 Now-- Now, tha--

11:13.439 --> 11:14.872
 This is going
 just too far.

11:14.908 --> 11:16.207
                [DOORBELL RINGS]

11:16.242 --> 11:17.609
                 [SQUEALS]

11:17.644 --> 11:19.043
Oh, no, you don't.
No, you don't!

11:19.079 --> 11:20.211
       [STAMMERS]
         Now--

11:20.246 --> 11:21.679
Jeannie, no,
no, no!

11:21.715 --> 11:25.216
          Jeannie. Will you just
              calm down, hm?

11:26.720 --> 11:27.685
                  Yes?

11:27.721 --> 11:29.153
                  MAN:
       Delivery for Mrs. Nelson.

11:29.188 --> 11:30.655
    [SQUEALS]
               Mrs. Nelson?!

11:31.691 --> 11:32.790
                    Where do you
                     want these?

11:32.826 --> 11:34.859
Back at the store.
            I'll take them.

11:34.894 --> 11:36.928
              Sign this, please.
        What's going on here?

11:36.963 --> 11:38.630
A woman should have
the kind of wardrobe

11:38.665 --> 11:42.467
that makes her feel successful,
alluring and irresistible.

11:42.502 --> 11:43.468
                    Yeah.

11:43.503 --> 11:45.035
The mink coat
will arrive tomorrow.

11:45.071 --> 11:47.271
    Mink coat? Where did you get
       the money for all this?

11:47.306 --> 11:48.739
Chapter three:

11:48.775 --> 11:50.508
"How to Open
a Charge Account."

11:50.543 --> 11:51.909
          Yeah, well, I want you
                 to forget

11:51.945 --> 11:53.210
                 this subversive
                   literature.

11:53.245 --> 11:54.378
            All those boxes go--

11:54.413 --> 11:55.813
                Go straight back
                  to the store.

11:55.849 --> 11:57.915
      I don't know how you think
       I'm gonna have the money

11:57.951 --> 11:59.216
                to spend on this
                 kind of thing.

11:59.251 --> 12:01.919
          Jeannie, it's-- I just
            can't afford this--

12:01.955 --> 12:03.454
                    Jeannie...

12:03.490 --> 12:04.489
You are pleased?

12:04.524 --> 12:06.123
            Pleased?

12:07.226 --> 12:09.126
         Oh, you're beautiful.

12:11.531 --> 12:14.365
I may keep
the gown?

12:14.400 --> 12:15.833
                   Is it...

12:15.869 --> 12:17.368
very expensive?

12:17.403 --> 12:19.103
                 Insanely.

12:20.439 --> 12:21.906
You may keep the insanely.

12:21.941 --> 12:23.975
             A-and the slippers?

12:24.010 --> 12:26.443
   And the slippers.
            A-a-and the perfume?

12:26.479 --> 12:27.678
       [SNIFFS]

12:27.714 --> 12:28.813
   And the perfume.

12:28.848 --> 12:30.648
                   [SQUEALS]

12:30.683 --> 12:32.850
           Thou art all heart.

12:38.290 --> 12:40.958
You didn't learn that
from reading any magazine.

12:40.994 --> 12:42.627
               You hungry?

12:42.662 --> 12:43.961
 Famished.

12:43.997 --> 12:45.095
            [CHUCKLES QUIETLY]

12:45.131 --> 12:46.597
What will we have?

12:46.633 --> 12:48.365
               Champagne.
  Mm-hmm.

12:48.401 --> 12:50.034
      Caviar.
                  Mm-hmm.

12:50.069 --> 12:51.602
Filet mignon?

12:51.638 --> 12:53.470
               What next?
Oriental.

12:53.506 --> 12:55.606
        Uh, uh, fresh asparagus?
     Mm-hmm.

12:55.642 --> 12:56.841
               Uh, baked Alaska.

12:56.876 --> 12:58.976
          Yes.
                    [CHUCKLES]

12:59.012 --> 13:01.178
Uh, uh, Napoleon brandy
with the coffee?

13:01.213 --> 13:03.113
                         Mm-hm.
   [GIGGLES]

13:04.316 --> 13:05.282
      Well?

13:05.317 --> 13:06.851
                     Well, what?

13:06.886 --> 13:08.352
 Aren't you gonna
  conjure it up?

13:08.387 --> 13:10.922
                Oh, nay, master.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.457
              No more of those
            silly little tricks.

13:13.492 --> 13:15.826
             From now on,
      you will do the conjuring,

13:15.862 --> 13:18.829
           with the credit card.

13:36.615 --> 13:38.149
         Uh, why don't I order
            for both of us.

13:38.184 --> 13:40.184
           Uh, we'll have
         two filet mignons.

13:40.219 --> 13:41.352
We will have fish.

13:41.387 --> 13:43.720
                We-- Don't you
                 like steak?

13:43.756 --> 13:45.022
Lesson two:

13:45.058 --> 13:47.791
"You must be independent,
self-reliant, unpredictable

13:47.827 --> 13:50.194
without seeming obvious."

13:50.229 --> 13:53.064
             Ahem. We'll have
          two fillets...of sole.

13:53.099 --> 13:55.333
                   May I suggest
                    a white wine

13:55.368 --> 13:56.467
                  with the fish?

13:56.502 --> 13:57.969
                 A nice Chablis?

13:58.004 --> 13:59.470
              Yes, yes.
           That'll be fine.

13:59.505 --> 14:01.005
Oh, I will
have champagne.

14:01.040 --> 14:02.373
            Lesson number three.

14:02.408 --> 14:03.474
  No, five.

14:03.509 --> 14:05.676
"An expensive woman
is a popular woman."

14:06.612 --> 14:07.911
              Champagne, please.

14:07.947 --> 14:09.347
                      Very good.

14:10.916 --> 14:12.583
                Jeannie, I think
                 it's very nice

14:12.618 --> 14:13.784
                that you want to
                   learn more

14:13.819 --> 14:15.086
                   about modern
                 American women,

14:15.121 --> 14:17.155
         but a little knowledge
       can be a dangerous thing.

14:17.190 --> 14:18.856
Do you realize, master,

14:18.891 --> 14:21.826
that this is the first time
you have ever taken me out?

14:21.861 --> 14:24.095
I want it to be
a memorable occasion.

14:24.130 --> 14:25.729
            Oh, I'll remember it
                 all right.

14:25.765 --> 14:27.531
              I'll remember
         how beautiful you look.

14:27.567 --> 14:28.899
    [GIGGLES]

14:28.935 --> 14:31.469
Well, that is because I am
having such a wonderful time.

14:31.504 --> 14:32.470
                       Good.

14:32.505 --> 14:34.872
I have not
enjoyed myself so much

14:34.907 --> 14:37.408
since the night my master,
the sultan Harun al-Rashid,

14:37.444 --> 14:38.977
      entertained
 the great Marco Polo.

14:39.812 --> 14:41.179
                  You really met
                    Marco Polo?

14:41.214 --> 14:42.813
   Oh, indeed, yes.

14:42.849 --> 14:44.515
   We used to hunt
  wild boar together.

14:44.550 --> 14:45.649
               What was he like?

14:45.685 --> 14:47.318
Oh, he was a wild bore.

14:49.755 --> 14:52.156
   Are you sure you need this?

14:52.191 --> 14:54.458
            Yeah-- Oh, yes, yes.
                Pour, please.

14:56.829 --> 14:59.363
       [FANFARE PLAYING]

14:59.399 --> 15:01.532
           [APPLAUSE]

15:04.670 --> 15:06.136
                <i> Bonsoir,</i>
         <i> mesdames et messieurs.</i>

15:06.172 --> 15:08.239
            For your pleasure,
         the Tail of the Peacock

15:08.274 --> 15:10.808
   is happy to present a program

15:10.844 --> 15:13.411
     of authentic harem dance.

15:13.446 --> 15:15.145
[LOUDLY]
Oh, I used to
do those dances

15:15.181 --> 15:17.314
at parties
for the sultan.

15:18.951 --> 15:21.519
          Performed by
   the distinguished <i> artiste,</i>

15:21.554 --> 15:23.153
            Sadelia!

15:23.189 --> 15:25.890
           [APPLAUSE]

15:25.925 --> 15:27.992
  [HAREM DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

15:58.458 --> 15:59.957
       [CLINKING CYMBALS]

16:34.260 --> 16:36.794
In my day, she would be
flung to the crocodiles.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.262
        Shh, Jeannie,
            please.

16:47.440 --> 16:49.340
She has never been
a harem dancer.

16:49.375 --> 16:51.542
That girl is an impostor!

16:51.577 --> 16:53.177
                  [QUIETLY]
               Jeannie, please.

17:10.829 --> 17:12.496
She is not fit to dance
for an audience

17:12.531 --> 17:13.896
of camel drivers.

17:13.932 --> 17:15.532
              Be quiet, Jeannie,
                    please.

17:15.568 --> 17:17.800
I'll show you how the dance
should be done!

17:22.941 --> 17:25.409
All right, lady.
Now, we are going home.

17:25.444 --> 17:28.179
        Oh. She calls that
          harem dancing?

17:28.214 --> 17:29.280
                      <i> Monsieur!</i>

17:29.315 --> 17:30.814
I know, I know, I know.
We're going.

17:30.849 --> 17:32.449
              Not before you pay
                  your bill.

17:32.485 --> 17:34.318
Hm? Oh!
Sorry about that.

17:35.421 --> 17:37.488
Sorry about that?
Sixty-four dollars?!

17:37.523 --> 17:39.790
                 That includes
              the amusement tax.

17:39.825 --> 17:41.325
          We were not
            amused.

17:41.360 --> 17:42.893
                Neither were we,
                 <i> mademoiselle.</i>

17:42.928 --> 17:45.562
    She moves as gracefully
   as a dog scratching fleas.

17:45.597 --> 17:46.730
                 She is my wife.

17:46.765 --> 17:48.232
       Sorry about that.

17:48.267 --> 17:49.733
Here. Keep the change.

17:49.768 --> 17:50.868
   [MUTTERS]
    Come on.

17:54.373 --> 17:55.539
   [GIGGLES]

17:55.574 --> 17:57.474
         [MUSIC PLAYING
         AT HIGH SPEED]

18:06.619 --> 18:07.752
        [BOTH LAUGHING]

18:07.787 --> 18:09.720
             That's the funniest
              thing I ever saw.

18:10.890 --> 18:12.490
                 That poor girl.
  [CHUCKLING]
     Well,

18:12.525 --> 18:15.025
I am pleased that
it amused you, master.

18:15.060 --> 18:17.461
                    [CHUCKLES]
Where are we going
tomorrow night?

18:17.497 --> 18:19.597
                      Nowhere.

18:19.632 --> 18:21.532
Oh, but-- But there are
17 more lessons

18:21.567 --> 18:22.900
that I have not
tried out yet.

18:22.935 --> 18:24.067
                     Yeah, well,
                      forget it.

18:24.103 --> 18:25.536
                I don't think
            they had you in mind

18:25.571 --> 18:27.638
         when they wrote that
      magazine article, Jeannie.

18:27.673 --> 18:30.641
But... But I-I want to be
a typical woman.

18:30.676 --> 18:32.843
             Well, woman, maybe.
               Typical, never.

18:33.712 --> 18:35.679
   A woman, maybe?

18:35.714 --> 18:38.482
I have been practicing
for over 2000 years.

18:38.517 --> 18:40.851
   You just better keep right on
      practicing, young lady,

18:40.887 --> 18:43.120
       because a woman doesn't
    act the way you did tonight.

18:43.155 --> 18:44.688
               But your behavior
                  this evening

18:44.723 --> 18:45.990
                  was absolutely
                   disgraceful.

18:46.025 --> 18:47.691
         Oh, and let me tell you
             one more thing--

18:54.200 --> 18:55.900
        You still have
        a lot to learn!

19:35.240 --> 19:37.407
          Oh, Jeannie,
    I'm ready for breakfast.

19:37.443 --> 19:39.242
      Hey, how about
   conjuring up some...

19:40.412 --> 19:41.745
        bacon and eggs?

19:41.781 --> 19:42.813
            Uh...

19:48.654 --> 19:50.554
     Now, Jeannie, come on.

19:52.859 --> 19:55.292
You might have waited breakfast.

19:56.996 --> 19:58.428
        Let's see, uh...

19:58.464 --> 20:00.163
     "Demonstrator wanted.

20:00.199 --> 20:01.732
             "No...

20:01.767 --> 20:03.200
   "No experience necessary.

20:03.235 --> 20:05.135
    Sam's Discount Center."

20:07.607 --> 20:08.739
   Good morning.

20:08.774 --> 20:09.940
              Allah be with you.

20:09.976 --> 20:11.241
          Huh?

20:11.276 --> 20:13.243
               Ladies, gaze upon
                  the ultimate

20:13.278 --> 20:14.244
             in kitchen wonders:

20:14.279 --> 20:15.746
               the Miracle Oven.

20:15.781 --> 20:18.081
Well, what
about it?

20:18.117 --> 20:19.750
              Oh, what about it?

20:19.785 --> 20:21.652
                  Uh...well...

20:21.687 --> 20:25.489
         Uh, it-- Its wonders
     include an automatic timer,

20:25.525 --> 20:27.424
             electric clock,
        stainless-steel counter,

20:27.459 --> 20:28.792
                   built-in meat
                    thermometer,

20:28.828 --> 20:31.595
          an all-new, built-in
       Roasterama interior, heh.

20:31.631 --> 20:32.730
                    Uh, whatever
                      that is.

20:32.765 --> 20:33.731
             Eh...

20:33.766 --> 20:35.432
It's just like
all the others.

20:35.467 --> 20:36.433
Come on, Pauline.

20:36.468 --> 20:38.068
Let's try the shop
across the street.

20:38.103 --> 20:39.436
                     Oh, please,
                        wait!

20:39.471 --> 20:40.671
                   If you do not
                     fork over,

20:40.706 --> 20:42.072
                 I will not have
                  a commission.

20:43.175 --> 20:44.642
                 Oh, believe me.
                   Believe me.

20:44.677 --> 20:47.545
               This Miracle Oven
               is <i> truly</i> magical.

20:48.548 --> 20:50.313
        For instance?

20:50.349 --> 20:51.481
                     Well, uh...

20:51.517 --> 20:53.684
              i-it will cook
          whatever you desire...

20:53.719 --> 20:54.685
                     [SNAPS]

20:54.720 --> 20:55.719
                   ...instantly.

20:55.755 --> 20:57.087
         Instantly?

20:57.122 --> 20:58.622
                       I will
                    demonstrate.

21:13.805 --> 21:14.938
                It is done.

21:14.973 --> 21:16.740
I don't
believe it.

21:16.775 --> 21:18.442
                I will show you.

21:19.045 --> 21:21.011
[ALL GASPING]

21:21.047 --> 21:23.647
[CROWD CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

21:23.683 --> 21:26.516
 Did you see what I saw,
         Pauline?

21:26.552 --> 21:28.919
I think so,
Frances.

21:28.955 --> 21:30.721
           I think I'll buy one.

21:30.756 --> 21:32.522
         [ALL SHOUTING]

21:32.558 --> 21:34.424
     You wouldn't like it.

21:34.460 --> 21:36.794
   Now, really, ladies, we--

21:36.829 --> 21:39.697
       When you get home,
         it won't work.

21:39.732 --> 21:43.033
             WOMAN:
      Miss! Miss, I'd like
     to see it bake a cake.

21:43.069 --> 21:44.602
              ALL:
             Yeah.

21:44.637 --> 21:46.470
              All right.

21:49.008 --> 21:50.006
JEANNIE:
Oh.

21:52.311 --> 21:53.944
         Uh, what kind of a cake
              do you desire?

21:53.979 --> 21:56.113
Oh. Devil's food.

21:56.148 --> 21:57.180
                Food of a devil?

21:57.216 --> 21:59.783
PAULINE:
Oh. Well, chocolate cake?

21:59.818 --> 22:01.285
        With coconut icing.

22:01.320 --> 22:02.386
                   [SNAPS]

22:05.157 --> 22:06.923
      Here you are.

22:08.093 --> 22:09.059
         [ALL GASPING]

22:09.094 --> 22:11.027
WOMAN 2: That's fantastic.
            [WHISTLES]

22:11.063 --> 22:12.563
                     Do you know
                     what it is?

22:12.598 --> 22:13.897
     Sure.

22:13.932 --> 22:15.799
 It's a fraud.
 She's a phony!

22:15.834 --> 22:17.167
        [CROWD YELLING]

22:19.505 --> 22:21.505
           Pardon me, ladies.
           Pardon me, ladies.

22:21.540 --> 22:22.940
                Ladies,
            ladies, ladies--

22:22.975 --> 22:24.741
Ladies, will you please
don't be excited?

22:24.777 --> 22:27.478
It's just some little
misunderstanding, I'm sure.

22:27.513 --> 22:28.846
                   I was just
                pitching a demo,

22:28.881 --> 22:30.514
         so they would fork over
              a commission.

22:30.549 --> 22:32.182
  That discount store
   across the street

22:32.217 --> 22:33.684
    sent you here
   to make trouble.

22:33.719 --> 22:35.586
               Oh, no!
        Yeah, let's go, Jeannie.

22:35.621 --> 22:37.454
She's not going
anywhere.
              Oh, yes, she is.

22:37.490 --> 22:38.655
Don't let her get away!

22:38.691 --> 22:40.924
[WOMEN YELLING]

22:40.960 --> 22:42.459
              MAN:
       You can't do that!

22:43.329 --> 22:45.095
          [YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

23:24.270 --> 23:26.370
            Jeannie.

23:26.405 --> 23:27.837
      You've been in there
          all evening.

23:27.873 --> 23:29.206
       Now, come on out.

23:32.411 --> 23:34.378
Jeannie, there's no reason
      to be unhappy.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.247
It could have happened
     to anyone.

23:38.817 --> 23:41.852
               [SOBS QUIETLY]

23:41.888 --> 23:43.888
      It could not have happened
           to a modern woman.

23:45.491 --> 23:46.823
              You were right.

23:47.927 --> 23:50.160
                   I'm a failure
                    as a woman.

23:50.196 --> 23:51.862
Oh, you are not.

23:51.898 --> 23:54.431
               You're everything
               a man could want.

23:54.466 --> 23:57.100
            You're--
  You're warm and considerate.

23:57.135 --> 23:58.101
                   Affectionate.

23:58.136 --> 23:59.603
          Oh, master.

23:59.638 --> 24:01.738
       You need an outlet
 for all that affection in you.

24:01.774 --> 24:04.108
   Oh, that is what I've been
      trying to tell you.

24:04.143 --> 24:05.843
          And I have the answer.

24:05.878 --> 24:07.111
            Oh. Yes?

24:07.146 --> 24:08.846
             You need a pet.

24:08.881 --> 24:10.413
             A pet?

24:10.449 --> 24:14.084
      Yeah. You know, like a dog
        or a cat or a parakeet.

24:14.120 --> 24:16.053
                Did you ever own
               a pet back there?

24:16.088 --> 24:18.222
         Oh, yes. Once.

24:18.257 --> 24:19.857
       His name was Sim.

24:19.892 --> 24:21.558
   The sultan gave him to me.

24:21.593 --> 24:23.460
         Good. Well, first thing
            tomorrow morning,

24:23.495 --> 24:24.761
                   you run down
                 to the pet shop

24:24.797 --> 24:26.497
                    and get one
                  just like him.

24:26.532 --> 24:27.898
         Or better yet,
        why don't you...

24:27.933 --> 24:29.099
        fetch old Sim here?

24:29.134 --> 24:31.869
Oh, master, thou art brilliant.

24:35.274 --> 24:37.474
   Ohh.
                     [NERVOUSLY]
                       Ah, ha.

24:37.509 --> 24:38.475
                Yeah.

24:38.510 --> 24:40.077
            [SNORTS]

24:40.112 --> 24:41.745
  [SIGHING]
     Oh.

24:41.780 --> 24:43.080
    Ooh.

24:48.220 --> 24:51.588
             [♪♪♪]
